Full Name: Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders - Fifth Edition - Text Revision
Author: American Psychiatric Association (APA)
Recommended?
It actually depends on who you are or what you are doing. This book includes the most complete set of psychiatric disorders under ICD diagnosis. It includes detailed introduction and diagnostic tips on the disorders. However, I do not see any reason someone would need this other than as a list of disorders to reference or as a diagnostic manual.
If you are conducting research, this book will act as a reliable source of diagnosis and examples.
